Message.Title: Why doesn't GOOG diversify it's $50B cash hoard?
Message.Msg: $50B is enough money to buy up every ounce of silver mined for the next four years globally! Why not buy SOME?!? It might be prudent to diversify about 10% or $5B into gold. The $50B is where? Treasury instruments? CDs earning 0.5%? LOL Do we really need to be childish enough to know that in a world where all central banks are printing and buying multi trillion dollar amounts of debt paper that the purchasing power has only one direction to go. I think silver is a better buy than gold because of its crucial industrial and technological uses. Solar, medical, investment bullion, the foundation has been laid for long term tightness. It doesn't take a genius to see that when our grandparents were our age there were TENS OF BILLIONS of ounces of silver circulating in the world. Today it is only a few hundred million readily available bullion and even that probably takes 3 months delivery as the Eric Sprott experience has proven. This is purely a function of that fact that silver demand and usage has been outpacing supply for many many years and is set to continue indefinitely. The fact there are millions of silver stackers in the world steadily adding to their holdings is going to put pressure on the price once the central planners' takedown has subsided. I am sure this post will be derided by the resident establishment trolls but it is a fact GOOG would be better off buying, say, $5B in gold, and a few hundred million ozs of silver and stashing it away and seeing what shakes out. It's NOT a radical idea, merely a rebalancing of less than 1/5th of GOOG current cash holdings. We see what happens when the Euro tanks, or the Yen tanks, or the Swiss Franc gets pegged and franc holders get swindled. Don't think it won't happen to every currency. They are all the same, except gold (and silver LOL.) I think they are definitely going to run GOOG to $1000 this year btw, but it's latecomer time now...
